               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18220911-206-person1970">
                  JOHN 
                  ELIJAH BLUNT
               <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1970" type="surname" value="ELIJAH BLUNT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1970" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1970" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Old-square, Lincoln's Inn. On the 20th of August, about seven o'clock in the evening, I was coming out of the archway leading from <placeName id="t18220911-206-crimeloc1095">Gray's Inn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-206-crimeloc1095" type="placeName" value="Gray's Inn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-206-crimeloc1095" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-206-off1093 t18220911-206-crimeloc1095"></join> to <placeName id="t18220911-206-crimeloc1096">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-206-crimeloc1096" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220911-206-crimeloc1096" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-206-off1093 t18220911-206-crimeloc1096"></join>, with my handkerchief in my pocket - I felt a pull at my pocket, turned round, and saw the prisoner and another man just behind me. I seized the prisoner, took the handkerchief from his hand, and gave him to a constable, who gave him to Read - the other ran into Holborn.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-206-person1971">
                  CHARLES 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1971" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1971" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-206-person1971" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard a cry of Stop thief! saw the prisoner running, followed, and secured him; he had got from the constable near Cross-street, Hatton-garden; the constable gave me the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was passing through the archway - several people were there, and the handkerchief was thrown against my breast; the gentleman turned round, and I gave it him immediately.</p>
